review_blob: good IPA but a bit too malty, the hops did not shine through. resin, citrus, alcohol, medium body, average carbonation, bitter
Not sure if this is a scotch...maybe a stout...had some booziness but overall it was a nice beer. the malts shine through. roasted barley and some chocolate and coffee notes.
light, refreshing and drinkable. bottle served at Bocadillas in Granada. Did not get to try their other offerings but this one was decent.

A nice change from Tona and Victoria. A light sessionable ale with some citrus zest and coriander on the nose and flavor. Spot on color and head for a light wheat ale. Very drinkable, my only complaint is it is a bit thin.

Suprised to come across this in Nicaragua. I like my beers hoppy and this did not disappoint. Solid Citrusy/Grapefruit hop profile with some tropical notes on the nose. I also got some resinous dank flavors that coated the tongue. Quite delicious. 
Overall, a very solid beer. This would hold its own back in the states.
